# Echologue - Project Context

This is a Next.js 15 ChatGPT-style app where users chat with AI about crawled webpage content.

## Documentation

Before making changes, consult the project docs in `docs/`:

- `docs/README.md` - Project overview and core concept
- `docs/architecture.md` - Tech stack, data flows, and file structure
- `docs/database.md` - Prisma schema, models, relationships, and migration logic
- `docs/features.md` - Feature specs (crawling, chat, auth, rate limits, UI/UX)
- `docs/api.md` - All API route definitions with request/response formats

## Key Decisions

- **Auth**: NextAuth.js v5 with Credentials provider (email/password), JWT sessions
- **Guest system**: cookie-based `guest_id`, 3 chats/day limit, migrated on login AND registration
- **Crawling**: fetch + JSDOM + Mozilla Readability; sub-link discovery with user selection (max 5)
- **AI context**: all ChatPage contents injected as system message per chat request
- **Streaming**: Vercel AI SDK `useChat` hook + `streamText()` with OpenAI GPT-4.1-nano
- **Chat ownership**: `Chat.userId` (registered) XOR `Chat.guestId` (guest), never both
